<p>Some reaction I‚Äôve received on Twitter is questioning why I care so much about a rattle. This machine cost 32,595 SEK (~$3,650 USD, ~¬£2,990 GBP, ~‚Ç¨3,400 EUR), and for that <em>ludicrous</em> amount of money, I expect a computer with all of its components attached together properly. I don‚Äôt think that‚Äôs unfair, and so far Apple customer support agrees with me.</p>

<p>The interesting question comes if <em>MBP #4</em> still rattles. While I‚Äôm fortunate that this machine isn‚Äôt (yet) my primary computer, I have a business to run and unfortunately I‚Äôm a Mac and iOS developer, which basically requires that I own a Mac. I <em>really</em> want this MacBook Pro to replace my iMac so I can have a more portable work machine, but if Apple can‚Äôt sell me a computer I‚Äôm happy with ‚Äî what then?</p>

<p>In the words of the greats: I‚Äôm not angry, I‚Äôm just disappointed. Maybe I should develop for Windows Phone instead.</p>

